The paper deals with the problem of extracting data from websites, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and database (cs.DB) research. The proposed method, XTPath, combines existing XPath with annotation extraction and informed search strategies, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) techniques.
